# Pattern Evaluation (LCP-UML-5)

Date: 2026-03-23

## Summary
- Total classes inspected: 19
- Classes exhibiting recognizable patterns: 12
- Pattern density: 12 / 19 = 0.63
- Decoupling & SOLID grade: C (controllers orchestrate persistence directly; no interfaces or domain services; inheritance used but lacks encapsulated behavior; some transactional safeguards present).

## Findings
| Component | Type | Pattern(s) | Notes on SOLID/Decoupling |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| BaseEntity | Abstract | Abstract Base Class | Shared identity/rowversion; good DRY but no domain behavior. |
| Account | Abstract | Abstract Base Class | Defines account contract; no strategy for balance rules; depends on concrete DbContext elsewhere. |
| SavingsAccount | Concrete | Inheritance (Account hierarchy) | Concrete data holder; business logic kept in controller; violates SRP. |
| CryptoWallet | Concrete | Inheritance (Account hierarchy) | Same as Savings; blockchain specifics not encapsulated. |
